Event_Description: The location ?Daneborg? is located in northwest Greenland. This fjord is ice covered 8-10 months a year, and during the ice-free period, the fjord receive large amounts of freshwater from melting snow enter from surrounding areas. This system is also a part of the Greenland long-term monitoring program.
IUCN_Habitat_type: 9 - Marine Neritic (Submergent Nearshore Continental Shelf or Oceanic Island)
